# Demo Cheat Sheet

## SLIDES

5. **Delegation Framework** — Understand, Plan, Delegate, Verify, Ship
6. **Plan Mode** — Review checklist (assumptions, scope, patterns, edge cases, testability)
7. **Primitives** — Rules are standards, Commands are shortcuts, Skills are playbooks, Subagents are specialists
8. **Anatomy of a Subagent** — Single responsibility, Clear trigger, Defined output, Tool awareness, Guardrails


## THE PLAN PROMPT (Act 2 → Act 3)

Pick one. All short enough to type or voice-to-text naturally.

**If starting from scratch (status reporter not yet built):**

> create a plan for adding an admin API endpoint to report unified storage migration status, delegating to subagents where possible

**If building on top of existing work:**

> plan out adding a frontend admin page that displays the unified storage migration status, use subagents to parallelize the work

**If using Jira integration:**

> pull down DEV-22 and plan it out, delegate to subagents where possible


## MOMENTUM PROMPTS (fire in ask mode while agents run)

Complete in under 15 seconds. Fill dead air, show semantic search, transition topics.

### Codebase intelligence (while subagents work)

> how does Wire dependency injection work in this repo?

> what pattern do existing admin endpoints follow for authorization?

> how does the dual writer mode work?

> what resources are currently auto-migrated to unified storage?

### Architecture (transitions or fill time)

> trace the request flow from an admin API call to the database

> how do the migration registry and migration definitions relate to each other?

### Quick visual wins (fast, interesting output)

> list all the unified storage migration definitions registered in this repo

> show me the admin route group and every endpoint registered under it

> what services does HTTPServer depend on?


## REHEARSAL BEATS

### Before you start
- [ ] Reset repo: `git reset --hard fork/cdiaz/unified-migration-status-reporter`
- [ ] Fresh agent panel (no prior conversations)
- [ ] Agent-first layout active
- [ ] Model set to your preference
- [ ] Slides 5–8 ready

### Act 1: Know (2 min)
- **Slide 5** — Delegation Framework (show before prompting)
- Talk track: "Today I'll walk through how Cursor lets you manage agents like an engineering team"

> explore the unified storage migration system and what work is in progress — use subagents

- While running → talk about indexing, semantic search, 20k files indexed
- When subagents appear → "I just delegated exploration to a specialist"
- Momentum fill if needed:

> what resources are currently auto-migrated?

### Act 2: Plan (3 min)
- Switch to plan mode (shift+tab)
- **Slide 6** — Plan Mode checklist (show while plan generates)

> create a plan for adding an admin API endpoint to report unified storage migration status, delegating to subagents where possible

- When plan appears → review aloud, call out 1 assumption to correct or confirm
- Transition: "this plan is our contract — now watch what happens when we hand it off"

### Act 3: Delegate — THE PEAK (4 min)
- **Slide 8** — Anatomy of a Subagent (show briefly before hitting build)
- Hit build
- Watch for subagents to spawn (expect: test-writer, api-designer, security-scanner, docs-updater)
- Click into 1-2 subagents to show their work
- Momentum fill:

> how is auth handled on admin routes?

- Talk track: "one prompt, multiple specialists — the plan told it what to delegate"

### Act 4: Verify (2 min)
- Show review/find issues on the changes
- Show bugbot on a sample PR (or talk through it)
- Transition: "we don't ship without review"

### Act 5: Ship (2 min)

> /create-pr

- Show CI watcher if time
- Transition: "from idea to PR in one session"

### Primitives tour (3 min, flex)
- **Slide 7** — Primitives (Rules, Commands, Skills, Subagents)
- Show .cursor/agents/ directory — "here's the team we built"
- Show .cursor/rules/ — "these are always-on guidelines"
- Show marketplace — "you don't have to build from scratch"
- Talk track: "start with rules, graduate to skills, build subagents when you need autonomy"

### Escape hatches
- Agent takes too long → momentum prompt in ask mode, keep talking
- Subagents don't auto-spawn → "let me invoke one directly":

> /security-scanner review the changes on this branch

- Plan looks off → "this is exactly why we use plan mode — catch it before it becomes code"
- Build fails → "debug mode is designed for exactly this" → pivot to debug mode
